#!/usr/bin/env bash
# i2pd-node help — usage information for i2pd-node(1).

cat <<EOF
i2pd-node(1) — manage an I2P daemon for anonymous networking

USAGE
    i2pd-node daemon <subcommand> [args]

SUBCOMMANDS
    lifecycle:
        start       bring up i2pd daemon (via launchd/systemd)
        stop        graceful shutdown
        restart     stop + start
        status      health check (running/down)
        monitor     tail the daemon log (default: -f)

    setup:
        install     install i2pd binary (brew|apt)
        enable      install + configure as system service
        disable     stop service and remove unit

    self-hosted reseed (bootstrap without public reseed servers):
        reseed-export
            Export routerInfo files for seeding (creates tar.gz)
        
        reseed-server
            Configure i2pd as floodfill reseed server
        
        reseed-bootstrap <url>
            Bootstrap from custom reseed URL

DESCRIPTION
    Tier 2 (Network Privacy) tool. Provides a local I2P router for
    applications to connect to I2P network on-demand (opt-in).

    Applications connect to:
        - SOCKS5 proxy: 127.0.0.1:4447 (for .i2p addresses)
        - HTTP proxy:   127.0.0.1:4444
        - SAM bridge:   127.0.0.1:7656
        - Web console:  http://127.0.0.1:7070

    No forced routing — applications opt-in to I2P routing.

SELF-HOSTED RESEED WORKFLOW
    Public reseed servers are often unreliable. Bootstrap from your
    own Apache web server instead:

    1. Ensure Apache is running:
       
       # macOS (built-in)
       sudo apachectl start
       
       # Linux
       sudo apt install apache2
       sudo systemctl start apache2
    
    2. On a server with working I2P connectivity:
       
       i2pd-node daemon reseed-export
       # Exports to: /Library/WebServer/Documents/i2pd-reseed/ (macOS)
       #          or: /var/www/html/i2pd-reseed/ (Linux)
       
       # The files are now in Apache's document root
       # No upload needed - already served!
    
    3. Bootstrap this machine from your server:
       
       i2pd-node daemon reseed-bootstrap http://yourserver.com/i2pd-reseed/
    
    4. Optional: Become a reseed server yourself:
       
       i2pd-node daemon reseed-server
       # Configures floodfill mode + daily cron job
       # Serves from Apache's document root

    Environment variables:
        I2PD_WWW_ROOT    Override Apache document root
        APACHE_USER      Apache user (default: www-data/wheel)
        APACHE_GROUP     Apache group (default: www-data/wheel)

EXAMPLES
    # Install and enable I2Pd
    i2pd-node install
    i2pd-node enable

    # Start the daemon
    i2pd-node start

    # Check status
    i2pd-node status

    # Access I2P web console
    open http://127.0.0.1:7070

    # Monitor the log
    i2pd-node monitor -f

    # Self-hosted bootstrap (when public reseeds fail)
    i2pd-node daemon reseed-bootstrap https://yourserver.com/i2p/

FILES
    /opt/local/etc/i2pd/i2pd.conf      I2Pd configuration (macOS)
    /opt/local/var/lib/i2pd/           I2Pd data directory (macOS)
    /Library/WebServer/Documents/i2pd-reseed/  Reseed files (macOS Apache)
    /var/www/html/i2pd-reseed/          Reseed files (Linux Apache)

SEE ALSO
    bitcoin-node(1), lightning-node(1), tor-node(1), ipfs-node(1)

FEAT-310 — Tier 2 privacy tools
EOF